snippet.textDisplay: I think my sister was 5 when our mum told us our cousin had gotten her first proper girlfriend and that we would be meeting her. In Norwegian there is just one word for both boyfriend and girlfriend- kjæreste (dearest) so my mum said my cousin had gotten a girl kjæreste. My sister looked at her thoughtfully for like a second and then said "ah, thats nice". After she asked me how my cousin, a girl, could have a girlfriend- and I said "they just both like each other" and my sister answered "oh okay, cool!!" It's legit that easy to explain to a kid

Hahahahahaha! In our group of friends/chosen family, flipping the bird is merely a freshly made traditional family greeting. If I want to insult someone, I give them the feather (pinky finger) because they aren't worth the whole bird. OR I say "UNf**k you! Why should you have any fun?"


RE: Buttslap. It doesn't matter where he was aiming. People need to keep their hands to themselves unless invited, especially where strangers are concerned. What if he HAD hit her in the back not knowing she has a medical implant or back issues? I've got an implant in my back and just bumping it is pretty painful. I don't even want to know what a full-on hit to its location would do. Plus a back slap like could that potentially put someone with a bad back or leg issues on the ground. Intent doesn't negate the action or the way the action affects the person on the receiving end. People saying it's not a big deal need to STFU. If this had happened in an office there would be no debate. A person who works in public rather than an office still has the right to do their job unmolested.


RE: Hallmark. They show hetero huggy-poo kissy-face content aplenty in their programming so that bit about PDAs not making their cut is nothing but pandering to the ultra-conservatives. I despise those who pander to the closed-minded and are wishy-washy on matters which shouldn't be a problem to begin with. Besides, I really wouldn't consider a kiss at a wedding a PDA anyway. That's a private event. So their own wording makes their lackluster supposed reason for the removal invalid. Semantics sometimes do matter. Not surprised about this considering the roasting they got for their "Jewish" Hallmark Movies. I'm guessing their tockings are getting some coal this year. LOL
